+In command mode, `v`, `V`, and `Ctrl-V` start character, line, and block visual selection in the
+focused pane. Visual mode uses `h`, `j`, `k`, and `l` or arrow keys to move the selection cursor.
+`y` copies the selected text, `Y` copies the selection linewise, and `Y` without an active visual
+selection copies the focused line. Copies are emitted to the terminal clipboard with OSC 52 and the
+selection is also available to the UI harness for automated checks.
